<main>
Hi, hi, yes: it’s me. Shreya. It’s such a pleasure to cross paths again. In the same timezone, in the same place. Welcome back to the city!

Wow. Your reputation really does proceed you, I remember your suits being special, but this one is another level. You must be turning heads and stopping traffic. Sorry, I know you’re a down-to-business person. I should give you the headlines.

I’ve been managing your portfolio: it’s all pretty stable at the moment.

I took your instructions seriously. You are, after all, my most important client. And no, I don’t say that to everyone. 

I know your time is valuable. I’ve tried to do as much as I can independently. I've already acted on your two Moorgate investments, 84 is doing well, but there are other local opportunities I want to run past you. 

Some major openings have appeared across time in the city. We’re going to open the market tomorrow with a stronger portfolio than we have today, right? 

I know. I’m being a bit optimistic. Which reminds me, as your banker, I’ll always try to be realistic with you. Optimism is good in hospitals, but today I’m going to ask you to make some huge decisions. I’ve done as much research as I can, but my predictions can only take me so far. It’s much easier to track actual investments.

I will advise you as best I can, but ultimately your assets are traded with your sign-off, and you need to be prepared for the unexpected.

But you know this. Sorry, I don’t want to patronise you. If you weren’t ready to deal with the unexpected, you’d never make a deal! You wouldn’t be in the industry of prediction. And you wouldn’t be the best.


<<timed 60s>><<set $prevpass to $passage>><<goto "EI-06">><</timed>>

 
 
</main>
