<main><<set $tally to 0>>
 
Here’s our first stop. Market’s opened in the 1400s and I have some prime real estate for you. Some real deals to be found in 1449.

This is the Girdler’s Company. Weird name, but they make… let me check. They make Girdles. Belts, straps, fine leather goods, the best Medieval cords on the market: there’s whispers that they’re going to get the Royal Charter in 1450. And you can see the developments they’ve made to the building.

Keep that in mind. 1450 is really hot right now. I also have an opportunity round the corner, coming in at Armourer’s Hall. Take a look.

That’s a prime facade, a metallurgical gem in the heart of the City. This is another up-and-coming Medieval hot-spot. Apparently it’s the place to be for Brass and metal repair. Surely destined for Charter in the next five to ten.

You got it? I’ll crunch the numbers. Sec. Sec. Okay. I can get you a juicy stake in either the Armourer’s Hall or the Girdler’s Company. Both are coming in at 1449, almost identical share price and both asking for a quarter-century probation period.

You have space in your portfolio for one. Which will you close on?

